# Import Playbook (Cursor)

Convert an existing open source application into a Webex Integration Playbook for
Webex programmability (Teams, Meetings, Calling, Rooms, Contact Center).

**How to invoke:** Type `/import-playbook` in Cursor chat and include the GitHub repo
URL in your message. Example:
> `/import-playbook — please process https://github.com/example/some-tool`

The GitHub repo URL will be provided by the user in the chat message that invokes
this rule. Extract it from their message before proceeding.

---

Follow the full instructions in `docs/commands/import_playbook.md`.

**Cursor-specific notes:**

- Use Cursor's web fetch capability to retrieve files from the source repo. Construct
  raw content URLs in the format:
  `https://raw.githubusercontent.com/<owner>/<repo>/main/<filepath>`
  If `main` returns a 404, try `master`.

- Create all output files directly in the workspace using the editor. Do not attempt
  to run bash validation commands via terminal automatically — instead, after creating
  all files, output the validation commands in a code block and prompt the author to
  run them in the integrated terminal.

- Replace every instance of `<slug>` in the instructions with the slug derived from
  the repo name in Step 2. Replace every instance of `<ext>` with the appropriate
  file extension for the chosen source language.
